div.p:
2 That no man be permitted at ſuch meetings, (before or after choiſe made) to provide banquets, or make coſtly preparations, for their entertainment, by whom they are choſen: for, it is a kind of embracing his choſers; 
                  •
               nd to me it ſeems an unproper Complement (if nothing were corruptly intended) that he who confers the benefit, ſhould be at the charge of giving Thanks; for, he that is Elected undertakes the ſervice for his Electers.
